Node.js Express: Automated CI/CD on Amazon EKS

First used a slim base image in 2023, now updated to node:24-slim.

Project Overview
This repository features a Node.js 24 Express application integrated with an automated Jenkins CI/CD pipeline. The workflow ensures that every code change is automatically built, containerized using optimized Docker images, and deployed to a scalable Amazon EKS cluster.

Tech Stack
Runtime: Node.js 24
Framework: Express.js
CI/CD: Jenkins (Declarative Pipeline)
Containerization: Docker
Orchestration: AWS EKS
Image: jemimaht/nodeapp

Deployment Instructions
Local Setup
To run the application directly on your machine:
npm install
node index.js
The app will be accessible at localhost:3000.

Docker Execution
The application is packaged using a slim base image and runs as a non-root user for stability.
Build the production image: docker build -t nodeapp-prod:latest .
Run the container (Mapped to Internal Port 3000): docker run -p 3000:3000 nodeapp-prod:latest

Jenkins CI/CD Pipeline
The Jenkinsfile automates the following phases:
Build: Installs dependencies using npm ci for consistent builds.
Push: Tags and uploads the versioned image jemimaht/nodeapp:${BUILD_NUMBER}.
Deploy: Updates the EKS cluster deployment using kubectl set image + rollout status.

Kubernetes Configuration
Deployment is managed via two primary manifests:
deployment.yml: Manages the application lifecycle and replica count.
deploymentservice.yml: Exposes the app via a LoadBalancer on Port 5000.
Manual Commands: kubectl apply -f deployment.yml && kubectl apply -f deploymentservice.yml

